In blitzscaling, firms and companies are given 5 different sizes. 
  The first is Family, which is a range of 1 to 9 employees.
  The second is Tribe, which is between 10-99 employees
  The third is Village, which is between 100-999 employees
  The fourth is City which is 1000 to 9999 employees
  The fifth and last one is Nation, which is anything over 10000 employees
